annotationA: Serine/threonine-protein phosphatase 4 regulatory subunit 2; Regulatory subunit of serine/threonine-protein phosphatase 4 (PP4) (By similarity). The probable PP4 complex Pp4- 19C-PPP4R2r-flfl (PPP4C-PPP4R2-PPP4R3) is required to prevent caspase induced cell death (in vitro)
annotationB: Serine/threonine-protein phosphatase PP2A 65 kDa regulatory subunit; The PR65 subunit of protein phosphatase 2A serves as a scaffolding molecule to coordinate the assembly of the catalytic subunit and a variable regulatory B subunit
